-- HIGHLIGHTS-Draghi comments at ECB news conference 
-- 
-- Thu Jul 03, 2014 08:33AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, July 3 (Reuters) - The European Central Bank left interest rates unchanged at record lows on Thursday, holding fire while it assesses the impact of a barrage of measures launched last month to pep up the flagging euro zone economy.

Following are comments by ECB President Mario Draghi at a post-meeting news conference.  MODERATE RECOVERY "The latest information signals that the euro area economy continued its moderate recovery in the second quarter with low rates of inflation and subdued monetary and credit growth."